---
layout: layouts/base.njk
order: 0
eleventyNavigation: Home
title: Swiss Sovereign AI — Fine-Tuned Apertus, Run in Your Jurisdiction
description: sysf.io fine-tunes Apertus — Switzerland's open LLM from EPFL, ETH Zurich and CSCS — on your documents and runs it inside your infrastructure. Open weights your auditors can inspect, no US API in the loop, and you own the model.
faq:
  - q: What is sysf.io?
    a: sysf.io is a Swiss sovereign-AI engineering studio. We fine-tune Switzerland's open Apertus model on your data and ship it as a production system — retrieval, agents and guardrails wired to your systems, deployed in Swiss or EU jurisdiction, or fully on-premise. You own the weights and the runbooks.
  - q: Which model do you use — is it always Apertus?
    a: Apertus is our default — Switzerland's fully open, fully transparent multilingual LLM from EPFL, ETH Zurich and CSCS, the one base whose weights <em>and</em> training data your auditors can inspect. But sovereignty isn't only Swiss. Where your compliance allows it, a European base like Mistral or an international one like Qwen can enter the evaluation and ship if it wins — all of them running inside your jurisdiction with weights you own. Which model within the tier your policy permits is decided by the evaluation, not the logo. The <a class="link-underline" href="/concepts/small-models/">model-choice guide</a> lays out the full spectrum.
  - q: Does our data ever leave our environment?
    a: For Production and Air-gapped engagements — no. Training and inference run inside your tenancy or your datacentre, with no third-party LLM APIs and no data egress. Pilots run in your environment or a dedicated single-tenant Swiss cloud — the data-handling options are on the <a class="link-underline" href="/pricing/">pricing page</a>.
  - q: How is this "compliant by design"?
    a: Open weights give you transparency and auditability; in-jurisdiction deployment addresses the Swiss Federal Act on Data Protection (FADP/nFADP) and EU GDPR; and documented data lineage plus guardrails support your EU AI Act obligations. We deliver the compliance and audit documentation alongside the model.
  - q: What does "end-to-end" mean here?
    a: We take a use case from data preparation and fine-tuning through evaluation, guardrails, deployment, monitoring and ongoing iteration. You get a maintained production system with agent orchestration, retrieval (RAG) and tools wired to your systems — plus a support and maintenance agreement — not a proof-of-concept that stalls.
  - q: How do we start?
    a: Engagements start with a fixed-scope Pilot on a single high-value use case — prove the numbers on your own data, then decide about production with an evaluation report in hand. Book a call and we'll scope it with you.
---
